cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about evaluating and comparing different methods for discourse coherence on a new corpus of real-world texts. The focus is on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given the emphasis on neural models and language processing, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI and cs.IR. Cs.NE is also a possibility given the use of neural models.
